Pattern 2: Dynamic / Variable-Size Window (Shrinkable)
The window size expands dynamically until a condition is broken, then shrinks from the left until the condition becomes valid again.

1. Easy: Minimum Size Subarray Sum (LeetCode 209) 
The Concept: 
Find the minimal length of a contiguous subarray of which the sum is >=target.

Java Code Blueprint:
public int minSubArrayLen(int target, int[] nums) {
    int left = 0;
    int currentSum = 0;
    int minLength = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
    
    for (int right = 0; right < nums.length; right++) {
        currentSum += nums[right]; // 1. Expand window
        
        // 2. Shrink window from the left as long as condition is met
        while (currentSum >= target) {
            minLength = Math.min(minLength, right - left + 1);
            currentSum -= nums[left]; 
            left++; 
        }
    }
    return minLength == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? 0 : minLength;
}
